    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted, drain your <strong>king prawns</strong> then add to the pan with the <strong>remaining garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped courgette</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the prawns are cooked through – these are your <strong>garlic king prawns &</strong> <strong>courgette</strong></p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and stir through most of the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save some for garnish!)</p>",
